race.comment: STEALTH OF NIGHT (16) is a progressive sort who looks to have found another nice target. She's won her past two up on speed, and drops 4.5kg off the last start win at Sandown Lakeside going from a BM70 to a BM84. Drawn low, she lands in the perfect spot again and should measure up. HARRY'S YACHT (1) found 1600m a bridge too far at Flemington last time. He did set up a strong pace there but struggled late having won well over this trip at Geelong prior. Back in trip should suit better and his best rates well. PORTER (9) led by a big space at Flemington last time and pinched a winning break, running good overall time. Drawn very wide here, expect he tries to keep rolling to the top and get them chasing again. ZOUPER FUND (6) is building a great record, winning fresh and good again at Cranbourne last time. 1400m is new territory but it should be fine. CODIGO (15) is consistent and should be thereabouts again.
